Formerly Lua2D/lua-wasi (pinned v0.1.0, 9d14360, here); the project was
renamed to andy-emerson/lua.wasm and 0.2.0 sunset the selective-AOT path
(luaot), returning the core to the verbatim stock Lua 5.4 interpreter.
This build never linked AOT (-DLUA_AOT is unset; the pump speaks lua.h,
not the luaw_* reactor glue), so the drop shed only dead code.

Update procedure: pick the new commit, replace src/ wholesale with the
pinned commit's src/, update this file. Never edit files under src/ —
fixes go to lua.wasm and arrive by re-pinning (same rule as this repo's
own upstream relationship; see readme.md).

Provenance is CI-checked: the pump job diffs src/ against a fresh clone
of the repo at this commit, so a drifted or hand-edited drop fails loudly.
